    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "J o u r n a l P r e -p r o o f 3 In concordance, acro-ischemic skin lesions have been described in younger Covid-19 positive patients 7 . Despite the children's' general good health, the lesions typically have affected not all fingers or toes but an average 3 fingers or toes. The lesions have been multiple, several millimetres in size, initially starting as patch, then becoming bullae that may become covered with black crusts in their subsequent evolution. Complete restoration occurs in about 14 days.",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 134,
                    "end": 135,
                    "text": "7",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF7"
                }
            ],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "The direct effect of the virus on the skin is not evident. We attribute our cutaneous observations to hyperergic and hypersensitivity reactions to the infection or to a microcoagulopathy of the cutaneous vessels 8 .",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "We underline the role of skin preventive measures to include the use of emollients, barrier creams, and moisturizers to assist in preventing skin complications precipitated by preventive measures during the pandemic.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": "Conclusions"
        }
    ],
